According to Sky Sport Italia and La Gazzetta dello Sport, Juventus are not convinced about loaning Dejan Kulusevski to Milan and would rather send the Sweden international to Arsenal. Kulusevski could leave Juventus in the January transfer window with Milan, Everton and Arsenal reportedly interested in loaning the former Parma and Atalanta starlet. Sky Sport Italia and Gazzetta confirm the Rossoneri are interested in the 21-year-old, but the Old Lady would prefer to send the player abroad. Barcelona, Juventus Make Offers To Sign  Aubameyang On Loan Matt Turner To Join Arsenal As Manager Milan are among Juventus’ rivals for a top-four finish, so the Bianconeri fear they would reinforce the Rossoneri by loaning Kulusevski. The versatile winger is not a regular starter under Massimiliano Allegri, having played 972 minutes across all competitions. Kulusevski has scored two goals in 27 appearances this season. Juventus are also in talks with Arsenal for Arthur, but according to The Athletic, the Gunners board have decided against loaning the Brazilian for 18 months with an option to buy for circa €40m.